pod-nodename.yaml
Purpose: Direct pod assignment to a specific node (bypasses scheduler)
File: examples/01-nodename/pod-nodename.yaml
yamlapiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: nginx-nodename
  labels:
    app: nginx
    method: nodename
spec:
  nodeName: worker-node-1  # Direct node assignment - bypasses scheduler
  containers:
  - name: nginx
    image: nginx:1.24
    ports:
    - containerPort: 80
    resources:
      requests:
        cpu: "100m"
        memory: "128Mi"
      limits:
        cpu: "200m"
        memory: "256Mi"
Usage:
bashkubectl apply -f examples/01-nodename/pod-nodename.yaml
kubectl get pod nginx-nodename -o wide
Expected Result: Pod scheduled on worker-node-1

pod-nodename-invalid.yaml
Purpose: Demonstrates what happens when nodeName references non-existent node
File: examples/01-nodename/pod-nodename-invalid.yaml
yamlapiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: nginx-invalid
  labels:
    app: nginx
    method: nodename-invalid
spec:
  nodeName: non-existent-node  # This node doesn't exist - pod will be stuck
  containers:
  - name: nginx
    image: nginx:1.24
    ports:
    - containerPort: 80
    resources:
      requests:
        cpu: "100m"
        memory: "128Mi"
      limits:
        cpu: "200m"
        memory: "256Mi"
Usage:
bashkubectl apply -f examples/01-nodename/pod-nodename-invalid.yaml
kubectl get pod nginx-invalid
kubectl describe pod nginx-invalid | grep -A 5 Events
Expected Result: Pod stuck in Pending state

deployment-nodename.yaml
Purpose: Shows why nodeName is bad for deployments (all replicas on same node)
File: examples/01-nodename/deployment-nodename.yaml
yamlapiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: nginx-nodename-deploy
  labels:
    app: nginx-deploy
    method: nodename
spec:
  replicas: 3
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: nginx-deploy
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: nginx-deploy
    spec:
      nodeName: worker-node-1  # All replicas on same node - BAD practice!
      containers:
      - name: nginx
        image: nginx:1.24
        ports:
        - containerPort: 80
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: "100m"
            memory: "128Mi"
          limits:
            cpu: "200m"
            memory: "256Mi"
        livenessProbe:
          httpGet:
            path: /
            port: 80
          initialDelaySeconds: 10
          periodSeconds: 5
        readinessProbe:
          httpGet:
            path: /
            port: 80
          initialDelaySeconds: 5
          periodSeconds: 3
Usage:
bashkubectl apply -f examples/01-nodename/deployment-nodename.yaml
kubectl get pods -l app=nginx-deploy -o wide
Expected Result: All 3 replicas on worker-node-1 (single point of failure!)
